z. Anil went to his girlfriend (Sunita) and proposed to her for marriage on the same night. Apart from being a good actor, he is also a talented semi-classical singer and his given voice for songs like "Pyaar Kiya Nahi Jata" and the title track for Chameli Ki Shaadi (1986 Bollywood Comedy) He got married to Sunita (The love of his life), and they are blessed with three children. His role in the movie "Meri Jung" proved to be a turning point for him. Initially, he was asked for the villain role but ended up in a lead role. Anil launched a "Welcome" pop album in 1986, along with Salma Agha. Anil and Salma Agha have given their voice, and Bappi Lahiri has given his music. Anil'sl signature word is "Jhakaas". For the film Mr India, Amitabh Bachchan was the preferred choice for the maker, and Anil wore the same pair of clothes throughout the movie. Anil, with his impeccable performance in the film Tezaab, set the benchmark for the film fraternity. He trained for 7 months in Gym for the Nayak movie, where he had to perform a 3D fighting scene, and the scene became immensely popular after the movie's release. He did not shave his body, and the filmmakers thought to smear the whole body with mud. His first production film was Badhaai Ho Badhaai and later My Father, Gandhi, My Wife's Murder in 2005 and much more. Anil opened in the interview that it was very difficult for him to perform a fight scene having mud on his body. As Multani Mitti dried up in an hour, he had to apply and remove the mitti frequently during the shoot. Anil is the only actor who has been part of all Race movie series: Race Race 2 Race 3 He was given the role of intelligent-cum-comical police inspector called Robert D'Costa. Slumdog Millionaire was his first international movie. He performed the character of Prem Kumar, and the movie has bagged 8 academy awards in various categories. Anil, in a talk show with Preity Zinta, revealed that his first communication with Sunita had happened on the phone. He 